            <thetext>The API Viewer once handled the situation correctly where parameters, return 
values etc. were given as a type known to the property system. Somehow this 
does not seem to work anymore.

The API Viewer creates links for types like Decorator, Color etc.

The transfer also goes wrong from a property declaration like &quot;BackgroundColor&quot; 
to the setter like &quot;setBackgroundColor&quot;. The parameters are displayed as &quot;var&quot; 
in this case.

Inherited methods also forgot the types of their constructor parameters 
completely. This can been seen for example in the widget method 
&quot;renderSeparator&quot; which is inherited from the LayoutItem.</thetext>
